{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"912555b9-c37d-47d3-86ff-d8791649112a","content":"It's a simple change. In your project file, just **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- UseVSTest removed — Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**What this changes:**\n\n1. **Test runner:** Tests now run via `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` instead of VSTest.\n2. **CLI:** Use `dotnet test` as before, but you can also run the test project directly (`dotnet run`) since it becomes an executable.\n3. **`[TestMethod]` / `[TestClass]`** — no changes needed; MSTest attributes stay the same.\n\n**Watch out for:**\n- **`.runsettings`** — most settings carry over, but some VSTest-specific options may need updating.\n- **Custom VSTest adapters/extensions** — these won't load; look for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n- **CI scripts** that parse VSTest TRX output — TRX is still available via `--results-directory`, but the default output format differs.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7655d8eb-6256-4aba-bc32-e37901bde968","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The repository doesn't have specific documentation about this migration. Let me answer based on my knowledge of MSTest.Sdk and the Microsoft.Testing.Platform migration.","outputTokens":385,"requestId":"0C0E:3DCCC3:2248AF:281582:69F00536"},"id":"8c18ab96-8706-408a-a82c-30003f4abc6a","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:54:24.489Z","parentId":"7920aa55-7382-4337-98f8-04ce87aec5e1"}
